<p><b>What are the 4 R's of the ideal apology?</b> Experts like Aaron Lazare and Nick Smith, in their book On Apology, point to four essential parts of the apology, and we can remember them as the 4 R's: Recognition, Responsibility, Remorse, and Reparation.</p>
<p><b>What is the apology paradox?</b> The paradox arises because apologising can reinforce negative attitudes or behaviours and even lead to further harm or misunderstanding.</p>
