<p><b>What is the apology language theory?</b> Recognizing how another person apologizes can preempt misunderstandings and facilitate conflict resolution. So-called "apology languages" include expressing regret and accepting responsibility, among others. Gestures of remorse or acts of restitution are a testament to the resilience and depth of human connection.</p>
